According to a report by Intel Market Research, the Europe Nickel Sulfate Market was valued at USD 0.32 billion in 2023 and is projected to grow from USD 0.35 billion in 2024 to USD 0.68 billion by 2032, registering a CAGR of 8.7% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing strong growth driven by Europe's rapid transition toward electric mobility, expanding lithium-ion battery manufacturing capacity, and increasing investments in localized battery material supply chains. Nickel sulfate remains a critical raw material for high-performance Nickel Manganese Cobalt (NMC) and Nickel Cobalt Aluminum (NCA) battery chemistries, supporting the production of long-range electric vehicles and advanced energy storage systems.
